ARIA attributes — aria-label, aria-expanded, aria-hidden (plain, concrete)
aria-label="Open navigation"

Tells screen readers what the button does. If the button only has an icon, screen readers need text to speak.

Plain: “If a blind person uses a screen reader, it will say ‘Open navigation’.”

aria-expanded="false" / "true"

Shows whether a control that expands/collapses something is currently expanded.

When the menu is closed: aria-expanded="false". When open: aria-expanded="true".

Screen readers announce the state, so users know whether the menu is open.

aria-hidden="true" / "false"

Put on the sidebar element to tell assistive tech whether it’s visible.

When menu is hidden: aria-hidden="true" (screen readers ignore the menu items).

When shown: aria-hidden="false" (screen readers can read the menu items).

This is important so keyboard/screen-reader users don’t accidentally navigate to hidden item
